{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe pattern only pays off if future sessions can discover and reuse it. A first-class doc is\nhow the next agent adds an ensure correctly, understands the invariants, and knows the\naccepted trade-offs and the A-tier future.\n\n## What\nWrite `docs/migrations.md` AND add a link to it from the docs index and CLAUDE.md. Cover: how\nto add an ensure unit (append to the `ensures.py` registry with a stable id + a check-then-act\ncallable returning ok/changed/failed); the entry points (init/re-init, `rebar fsck --repair`,\nMCP server startup — all reconcile unconditionally under the write lock); the applied-set\n`.ensure-applied` marker + the `.ensure-hinted` rate-limited pending-hint; the\nmarker-gates-hint-never-repair invariant; the hot-path performance contract (no sweep on\nwrites; ≤1 marker read/process); the ACCEPTED long-lived-MCP trade-off (converges at boot,\ndoes not re-sweep mid-life — drift caught at next `fsck --repair`); and the A-tier future\n(committed store-format version + ordered ledger, fail-closed on too-new) with the\ncommitted-version recommendation. Use gc-config as the worked reference unit.\n\n## Scope\nIn: `docs/migrations.md` + the index/CLAUDE.md link. Out: code (WS1-3), tests (WS5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/migrations.md` documents adding an ensure unit (registry + stable id + check-then-act + typed result) with gc-config as the worked reference\n- [ ] Documents the entry points, `.ensure-applied` + `.ensure-hinted`, the pending-hint, and the marker-gates-hint-never-repair invariant\n- [ ] Documents the hot-path performance contract AND the accepted long-lived-MCP re-sweep trade-off\n- [ ] Captures A-tier future (committed store-format version + ordered ledger, fail-closed on too-new) + committed-version recommendation\n- [ ] A link to `docs/migrations.md` is added from the docs index and CLAUDE.md (verifiable: the link string is present in both)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783574712524717001,"uuid":"4a653387-6b2d-43d8-bc0b-794795d754b4"}